== Configuring Japanese Scripts in my Computer ==

Hi,

How to configure Japanese Scripts in my Computer? 
If there is any software available for the above purpose, can you please post the same?

Thanks.

:Hello, I think it would help to answer this question if you gave a little bit of information on the type of computer system you are using. i.e. Windows or Linux or Apple and which browser (Internet Explorer, Firefox, Chrome etc) and what their version numbers are.

Hills of Bigorre

Taken by [[User:Nathan Hamblen|Nathan]] in June of 2004

{{GFDL}}

{{cookdp}}
Recipes involving meatballs include:
*[[Cookbook:Fried Meatballs|Fried Meatballs]] *[[Cookbook:Swedish Meatballs|Swedish Meatballs]] * [[Cookbook:Italian Meatballs|Italian Meatballs]] * [[Cookbook:Spaghetti and Meatballs|Spaghetti and meatballs]] * [[Cookbook:Frikadelle (Meat Balls)|Frikadelle]] *

This book consists of a set of short tutorials on making period armour and chain mail.  We refer to items that are in or out of period in the context of which re-creation group we belong to.  In the case of the armours presented here, the operational time span is that of the Society for Creative Anachronism, or the SCA.  The 'uptime' cut-off date is 1600 CE, as the defining documents for the Society mandate a 'pre-16th century' mode of dress, etc.  We allow a bit of leeway to include the years up to the death of Elizabeth I, at 1603 CE.  The 'downtime' date(s) are a favourite argument topic; a rough estimate is 400 CE to 500 CE

'''Chapters''':

*[[/Making Basic Armour/]]
*[[/Making Period Leather Armour/]]
*[[/Making Period Mail/]]

